[LAUGHING]

26:49.006 --> 26:51.607
You made a real good impression
with Joe and the guys.

26:51.609 --> 26:54.141
He thinks you're
a real straight shooter.

26:54.143 --> 26:57.915
Yeah, well, I guess I got you
to thank for that.

27:00.049 --> 27:01.518
Listen, son.

27:04.488 --> 27:08.090
What I'm gonna tell ya,
goes no further.

27:08.092 --> 27:09.561
You understand?

27:11.594 --> 27:12.529
Yeah.

27:14.163 --> 27:15.400
Okay, then.

27:18.302 --> 27:20.071
We bustin' out.

27:23.172 --> 27:24.305
Who?

27:24.307 --> 27:26.176
Me, Joe, Sam and Marvin.

27:28.612 --> 27:31.412
Yeah, but no one's ever escaped
from this place, right?

27:31.414 --> 27:33.047
Well, some have tried.

27:33.049 --> 27:34.382
No one succeeded.

27:34.384 --> 27:36.854
First time for everything.

27:43.126 --> 27:46.027
- Where do I fit in in this?
- A plan like this?

27:46.029 --> 27:49.430
We could do with a guy
like you on the team.

27:49.432 --> 27:52.636
And you ain't gonna shoot your
shorts when the heat comes down.

27:57.141 --> 27:59.944
How long they give you,
anyways?

28:02.078 --> 28:03.513
Ninety-nine years.

28:05.215 --> 28:08.249
Eligible for parole after 30.

28:08.251 --> 28:11.255
Seems the right risk
to take then, huh?

28:19.063 --> 28:21.632
[PEOPLE CHATTERING
INDISTINCTLY]

28:32.142 --> 28:34.077
[♪♪♪]

28:51.428 --> 28:53.698
Take a seat, Clarence.

28:58.134 --> 29:01.636
I don't know if you know
or not but, uh...

29:01.638 --> 29:05.543
you're the youngest prisoner
we've ever had here at Alcatraz.

29:07.378 --> 29:09.276
Yes, sir.

29:09.278 --> 29:11.412
Now, you should also be aware

29:11.414 --> 29:14.985
that that's nothing
to be proud of.

29:16.420 --> 29:18.022
Of course, sir.

29:21.392 --> 29:23.492
Most of the prisoners
we have here

29:23.494 --> 29:26.328
will never
taste freedom again.

29:26.330 --> 29:28.530
They will die
within these walls

29:28.532 --> 29:32.034
or within the walls
of another prison.

29:32.036 --> 29:35.405
You, however, have the chance
to be particularly unique.

29:37.574 --> 29:40.441
Given your age
and with an exemplary record

29:40.443 --> 29:44.014
of good behavior, parole is
still possible in your future.

29:47.817 --> 29:50.754
So with that in mind...

29:52.588 --> 29:54.790
do you really think
it's in your best interest

29:54.792 --> 30:00.198
to keep company with a murderer
and his associates?

30:02.332 --> 30:07.138
A man needs friends to survive
in a place like this, Warden.

30:09.105 --> 30:10.805
Rather naive of you
to consider

30:10.807 --> 30:15.379
a group of incurable
reprobates friends.

30:16.747 --> 30:19.214
But make no mistake,
Clarence,

30:19.216 --> 30:23.217
these criminals' loyalty
is based entirely

30:23.219 --> 30:25.419
upon personal gain.

30:25.421 --> 30:27.421
The moment
you cease to be useful,

30:27.423 --> 30:31.161
they will cast you aside
without another thought.

30:37.500 --> 30:40.537
With all do respect, Warden,

30:42.672 --> 30:45.242
why the sudden interest
in my well-being?

30:47.111 --> 30:49.844
You made it very clear
we're here to be punished,

30:49.846 --> 30:51.746
not rehabilitated.

30:51.748 --> 30:54.748
Yes, normally that is true.

30:54.750 --> 30:57.687
But as I said,
your case is unique.

31:00.591 --> 31:06.294
You see, Clarence,
obedience to authority

31:06.296 --> 31:08.399
is a biblical principle.

31:10.400 --> 31:15.303
As it says in Romans 13:2,
"Whosoever resists

31:15.305 --> 31:19.674
the authorities,
resists what God has appointed.

31:19.676 --> 31:24.549
And those who do so will
bring judgment upon themself."

31:26.749 --> 31:30.185
Now, by the grace of God,
I have been given

31:30.187 --> 31:33.690
the task of punishing
the prisoners of Alcatraz.

31:35.726 --> 31:37.425
Still,
like most human beings,

31:37.427 --> 31:40.829
I like to keep
a sliver of hope

31:40.831 --> 31:42.800
that some of them
can be reformed.

31:44.901 --> 31:46.901
Unfortunately,
hope to lead a civil life

31:46.903 --> 31:49.440
died for most of these men
many years ago.

31:51.575 --> 31:54.545
The question you need
to ask yourself, Clarence...

31:55.946 --> 31:58.649
is: What direction
do you wanna take?

32:04.621 --> 32:08.325
My hope is you will choose
a better life.

32:10.594 --> 32:15.830
And within these pages,
you can find a new direction

32:15.832 --> 32:18.800
that will lead you
to that life.

32:18.802 --> 32:22.236
By absorbing the wisdom
within these pages,

32:22.238 --> 32:28.342
you can find salvation
and repentance.

32:28.344 --> 32:31.149
But that is your choice,
Clarence.

32:32.716 --> 32:36.921
I suggest you begin with John,
24 to 26.

32:49.333 --> 32:50.567
That is all.

32:52.369 --> 32:53.603
Yes, sir.

33:04.614 --> 33:07.248
CLARENCE: <i>"So for the
second time, the Pharisees</i>

33:07.250 --> 33:09.784
<i>"summoned the man
who had been blind and said:</i>

33:09.786 --> 33:14.823
<i>"'Speak the truth before God,
we know this man is a sinner.'</i>

33:14.825 --> 33:17.592
<i>"'Whether or not he is
a sinner, I do not know.'</i>

33:17.594 --> 33:19.694
<i>"The man replied.</i>

33:19.696 --> 33:21.896
<i>"'All I know is this:</i>

33:21.898 --> 33:25.503
<i>once I was blind
and now I can see.'"</i>

33:26.737 --> 33:28.672
[PEOPLE CHATTERING
INDISTINCTLY]

33:37.613 --> 33:39.581
BERNIE:
See what he's trying to do?

33:39.583 --> 33:40.582
CLARENCE:
What?

33:40.584 --> 33:42.553
Turn you into a snitch.

33:44.054 --> 33:45.754
Look, I'm not a rat.

33:45.756 --> 33:47.788
Glad to hear that.

33:47.790 --> 33:50.592
Let me tell you a couple
of things, Clarence.

33:50.594 --> 33:52.694
Everything the guys
on the top do

33:52.696 --> 33:55.397
is designed to keep
the little guy down.

33:55.399 --> 33:57.631
Now, the warden,
he's at the top.

33:57.633 --> 33:59.868
He sees us
as the little guys.

33:59.870 --> 34:03.304
He's trying to plant those seeds
of fear and paranoia.

34:03.306 --> 34:05.674
Make us turn against
each other.

34:05.676 --> 34:07.645
JOE:
Bern?

34:09.379 --> 34:12.379
Can you give me and Clarence
a couple of minutes?

34:12.380 --> 34:14.317
[SEAGULLS CHIRPING]

34:26.629 --> 34:28.297
Come here, kid.

34:37.808 --> 34:41.679
So Bern tells me he told you
about the thing.

34:43.612 --> 34:44.947
He mentioned it, yeah.

34:46.917 --> 34:50.685
Well, if you want in,
I gotta make sure

34:50.687 --> 34:52.853
you're a stand-up guy.

34:52.855 --> 34:54.723
I can't have a kid
bricking his pants

34:54.725 --> 34:56.091
and slowing us down.

34:56.092 --> 34:58.859
Look, that won't happen.

34:58.861 --> 35:02.899
That's good to hear but seeing
is believing, my friend.

35:04.134 --> 35:05.569
You know what I'm saying?

35:06.803 --> 35:09.636
So, what do you
want me to do?

35:09.638 --> 35:13.310
There's a guy in cell block A,
Micky Dallesandro.

35:15.745 --> 35:17.314
He owes me some money.

35:18.448 --> 35:20.147
You want me to collect?

35:20.149 --> 35:23.553
No, that ship has sailed.

35:24.754 --> 35:26.523
Final notice time.

35:27.156 --> 35:28.591
Final notice?

35:29.493 --> 35:30.628
Yeah.

35:36.665 --> 35:39.000
How would I, uh...
How would I do it?

35:39.002 --> 35:41.469
Sam will take care of
the weapon.

35:41.471 --> 35:44.071
Well, why doesn't Sam just
take care of the whole thing?

35:44.073 --> 35:45.375
Look, kid.

35:46.942 --> 35:51.545
In my line of work, if you wanna
be part of the crew,

35:51.547 --> 35:53.049
you gotta make your bones.

35:54.584 --> 35:56.518
If you do this
little job for me,

35:56.520 --> 35:58.886
then I can relax,
knowing you have the stones

35:58.888 --> 36:00.123
for the bigger job.

36:04.794 --> 36:06.763
So when do you want it done?

36:08.832 --> 36:11.699
Sam will get the weapon
to you tomorrow.

36:11.701 --> 36:13.103
Point the guy out.

36:14.805 --> 36:16.841
Then it's up to you.

36:19.109 --> 36:21.145
Let me give you
a piece of advice.

36:22.446 --> 36:24.446
Do it quietly,

36:24.448 --> 36:26.480
watch the guy,

36:26.482 --> 36:28.016
pick your moment.

36:28.018 --> 36:30.618
In and out quickly
before anyone knows

36:30.620 --> 36:32.053
what the fuck happened.

36:32.055 --> 36:34.154
You make a song
and dance of this,

36:34.156 --> 36:36.393
you won't see daylight
for years.

36:37.993 --> 36:39.596
You know what I'm sayin'?

36:40.830 --> 36:42.031
Okay.

36:44.234 --> 36:45.466
Good.

36:45.468 --> 36:46.469
[SNIFFS]

36:47.603 --> 36:49.140
Bones and stones, kid.

36:51.241 --> 36:53.043
Bones and stones.

36:54.944 --> 36:57.212
[♪♪♪]

36:57.214 --> 36:59.150
[PEOPLE CHATTERING
INDISTINCTLY]

37:33.216 --> 37:34.582
What's this?

37:34.584 --> 37:35.783
Pass it on to the kid,

37:35.785 --> 37:38.185
he's fitting Dallesandro
for a suit.

37:38.187 --> 37:40.187
Says who?

37:40.189 --> 37:43.290
Joe gave the order,
Clarence agreed.

37:43.292 --> 37:45.527
Why the fuck
ain't you doin' it?

37:45.529 --> 37:47.694
Kid's gotta
make his bones, Bern.

37:47.696 --> 37:49.730
You know how it is.

37:49.732 --> 37:51.669
[SWEEPING LIGHTLY]

37:55.971 --> 37:58.107
Go on, that's enough.

38:06.850 --> 38:08.752
Can I have a word?

38:09.785 --> 38:11.120
What is it?

38:18.627 --> 38:21.498
You told the kid to put
the button on Dallesandro?

38:23.033 --> 38:24.899
You got a problem with that?

38:24.901 --> 38:27.167
Sam or Marvin couldn't do it?

38:27.169 --> 38:30.270
You don't think the kid's
got stones for it?

38:30.272 --> 38:34.174
Not sayin' that,
he's just so young.

38:34.176 --> 38:37.312
You brought him
into this, Bern.

38:37.314 --> 38:39.313
If he's old enough
to do the other thing,

38:39.315 --> 38:40.882
he's old enough to do this.

38:40.884 --> 38:43.116
He hasn't done this before.

38:43.118 --> 38:45.185
What?

38:45.187 --> 38:47.955
I don't know, what if it
doesn't go his way?

38:47.957 --> 38:50.591
Don't you think
you're taking the same risk

38:50.593 --> 38:52.826
by making him
part of the other thing?

38:52.828 --> 38:54.761
It's not the same,
it's different.

38:54.763 --> 38:56.931
He could get out,
start living his life again

38:56.933 --> 38:58.768
without wasting
30 fuckin' years.

39:00.703 --> 39:02.573
Why you pushin' this?

39:04.174 --> 39:06.110
I just don't think
he should do it.

39:08.944 --> 39:11.645
He's the least experienced.
Give me the job,

39:11.647 --> 39:13.616
and I'll take care of it,
no problem.

39:15.085 --> 39:19.020
Look, Bern,
I offered the job to the kid,

39:19.022 --> 39:21.955
he accepted it,
so let's just drop it, okay?

39:21.957 --> 39:24.391
- But Joe...
- [TRAY CLATTERS]

39:24.393 --> 39:26.960
You disobey an order
of mine again,

39:26.962 --> 39:29.966
and I will slit
your fuckin' throat.

39:31.667 --> 39:34.837
- Fuck.
- [CUP CLANGS]

39:42.379 --> 39:43.846
Yeah, yeah.

39:55.892 --> 39:57.594
[SIGHS]

40:03.667 --> 40:06.103
I'm supposed to
give you something.

40:07.837 --> 40:09.607
Something from Sam.

40:13.743 --> 40:14.745
Right.

40:18.281 --> 40:20.918
This sittin' well with you?

40:21.951 --> 40:23.654
It is what it is.

40:26.288 --> 40:29.190
You can be honest with me,
you know?

40:29.192 --> 40:31.629
What do you want me to say?

40:36.031 --> 40:37.234
Okay, then.

40:39.368 --> 40:40.870
I'm gonna level with you.

40:43.105 --> 40:45.339
Never told anyone
this before.

40:45.341 --> 40:46.777
What?

40:49.846 --> 40:51.982
I killed a few people
in my time.

40:53.315 --> 40:55.982
Business related.
Nothing personal.

40:55.984 --> 40:58.154
Not that that's any excuse.

41:01.223 --> 41:07.194
Thing is, every time
I pulled the trigger

41:07.196 --> 41:13.069
it's like a flame
inside of me flickered.

41:15.038 --> 41:16.940
It even went out once.

41:20.042 --> 41:23.446
It took me years
to get that relit again.

41:25.748 --> 41:27.817
Look, I know
this ain't gonna be easy...

41:29.819 --> 41:31.252
but this is the life.

41:31.254 --> 41:33.120
It doesn't have to be
your life, kid.

41:33.122 --> 41:35.388
This plan, if it works,
you'll get out of here.

41:35.390 --> 41:37.257
Go somewhere, start afresh.

41:37.259 --> 41:39.292
Forget about this
miserable fucking place

41:39.294 --> 41:40.730
and everything in it.

41:41.997 --> 41:43.797
It's a lot harder
to do that

41:43.799 --> 41:45.333
with a stain on your soul.

41:45.335 --> 41:48.870
That's what it feels like,
you know?

41:48.872 --> 41:52.373
Some guys can put a button
on a guy and feel nothing.

41:52.375 --> 41:53.944
But this...

41:56.078 --> 41:57.944
it stays with you.

41:57.946 --> 42:01.785
You don't know which one
you gonna be until you do it.

42:05.187 --> 42:06.355
I feel like...

42:08.190 --> 42:10.891
I feel like everywhere I go,

42:10.893 --> 42:13.326
I carry those ghosts with me.

42:13.328 --> 42:16.332
You don't wanna be haunted
like I am, trust me.

42:23.272 --> 42:25.241
If I don't do this
for Joe...

42:28.044 --> 42:29.913
what becomes then of me?

42:33.549 --> 42:35.583
Overnight,
my chances of survival

42:35.585 --> 42:38.085
in this place fuckin' plummet.

42:38.087 --> 42:40.023
[SEAGULLS CHIRPING]

43:10.285 --> 43:12.221
[PEOPLE CHATTERING
INDISTINCTLY]

43:25.335 --> 43:26.804
[SIGHS]

43:28.872 --> 43:32.408
[DOOR SQUEAKS]

43:43.953 --> 43:45.953
[URINE TRICKLING]

43:45.955 --> 43:47.891
[♪♪♪]

44:26.696 --> 44:28.194
[GRUNTS]

44:28.196 --> 44:29.529
Go, now.

44:29.531 --> 44:31.098
- But...
- Just go.

44:31.100 --> 44:33.234
Joe asked you
to do this, not me.

44:33.236 --> 44:35.038
You understand? Go!

44:40.676 --> 44:44.247
[DOOR SQUEAKS]

44:57.259 --> 44:59.395
How's it goin', Bern?

45:02.064 --> 45:03.165
Not bad.

45:04.334 --> 45:06.270
[SEAGULLS CHIRPING]

45:09.339 --> 45:11.541
Taking a bit of laundry,
man.

45:13.176 --> 45:14.378
Weird habit.

45:17.346 --> 45:18.547
Yeah.

45:23.319 --> 45:25.252
You know, the rumor mill
of this place

45:25.254 --> 45:27.520
is an interesting thing.

45:27.522 --> 45:31.060
Most of the time I don't
pay attention to it, but...

45:32.995 --> 45:38.165
sometimes it brews up something
that just catches your ear.

45:38.167 --> 45:39.303
Yeah?

45:41.738 --> 45:43.040
Like what?

45:44.439 --> 45:46.575
A friend with the laundry.

45:48.578 --> 45:52.482
Word around the campfire is
the kid didn't close the deal.

45:55.752 --> 45:57.421
I heard he couldn't do it.

46:00.455 --> 46:02.656
You know, you're becoming
a very strange man

46:02.658 --> 46:04.328
in your old age, Bern.

46:05.594 --> 46:07.297
What do you mean?

46:09.598 --> 46:12.068
You don't know
what I'm talkin' about?

46:14.169 --> 46:15.438
I'm sorry.

46:18.306 --> 46:19.442
No.

46:21.343 --> 46:23.446
[LAUGHING]

46:30.453 --> 46:32.122
All right, Bern.

46:35.223 --> 46:37.727
Let's get our head
in the game, shall we?

46:40.163 --> 46:41.732
Big day tomorrow.

46:52.075 --> 46:54.011
[♪♪♪]

46:56.379 --> 46:58.578
NARRATOR:
<i>Alcatraz, "The Rock,"</i>

46:58.580 --> 47:01.815
<i>the mighty escape-proof jail
in San Francisco Bay,</i>

47:01.817 --> 47:04.451
<i>dreaded by every
American lawbreaker.</i>

47:04.453 --> 47:06.719
<i>It is dusk
and within the prison,</i>

47:06.721 --> 47:09.156
<i>a mutiny
of hardened life-term killers</i>

47:09.158 --> 47:10.658
<i>has become war to the death.</i>

47:10.660 --> 47:12.759
<i>Armed with weapons
from the prison armory,</i>

47:12.761 --> 47:15.429
<i>the prisoners boast
they will shoot their way out.</i>

47:15.431 --> 47:18.535
<i>Nobody has yet escaped
from Alcatraz... alive.</i>

47:21.404 --> 47:24.138
I tried each one
at least three times.

47:24.140 --> 47:25.438
It ain't here.

47:25.440 --> 47:28.676
All right, get in here,
on your knees!

47:28.678 --> 47:30.377
On your fuckin' knees!

47:30.379 --> 47:32.081
On your fuckin' knees!

47:36.152 --> 47:37.487
[PANTING]

47:56.506 --> 47:57.574
LAGESON:
Joe?

47:59.542 --> 48:01.475
You need
to call this thing off.

48:01.477 --> 48:06.346
Listen to me, even if you did
have the keys to the yard,

48:06.348 --> 48:08.415
chances are
you'd get gunned down

48:08.417 --> 48:09.817
the moment
you stepped outside.

48:09.819 --> 48:12.620
Fuck that, Joe.
We come too far to go back.

48:12.622 --> 48:15.623
LAGESON: That ain't true,
no one's died yet.

48:15.625 --> 48:17.891
SAM: Don't buy that
horseshit, Joe.

48:17.893 --> 48:19.792
Don't listen to him Joe,
come on,

48:19.794 --> 48:22.263
you can change all this.

48:22.265 --> 48:24.265
No one needs to die today.

48:24.267 --> 48:25.466
Fuck him, Joe.

48:25.468 --> 48:27.667
If we can't get out,
let's burn

48:27.669 --> 48:29.703
this motherfucker
to the ground.

48:29.705 --> 48:32.373
Take as many bulls
with us as we can.

48:32.375 --> 48:38.379
Starkly, boys, you
start killing people now,

48:38.381 --> 48:41.248
and it will be a gas chamber
for all of you.

48:41.250 --> 48:42.882
- [PANTING]
- Joe, listen to me.

48:42.884 --> 48:45.486
We can get the warden
down here right now.

48:45.488 --> 48:48.321
All right,
shut the fuck up, all of you!

48:48.323 --> 48:50.424
I need to think!

48:50.426 --> 48:52.192
I can't think
with you prairie dogs

48:52.194 --> 48:53.729
hollering in my fucking ear!

49:03.638 --> 49:04.774
Fuck!

49:07.609 --> 49:10.243
How many guards
do they have hostage?

49:10.245 --> 49:11.645
Three.

49:11.647 --> 49:14.949
Lageson, Miller,
and Weinhold.

49:14.951 --> 49:16.419
Okay.

49:18.386 --> 49:20.654
Well, considering
the strategic disadvantage

49:20.656 --> 49:23.489
because of
the hostage situation,

49:23.491 --> 49:25.826
I don't think we have
sufficient custodial

49:25.828 --> 49:27.460
strength to move in again.

49:27.462 --> 49:29.862
But sir, w-we have
to rescue those men.

49:29.864 --> 49:31.998
For all we know,
they could be dead already.

49:32.000 --> 49:34.435
Precisely.
There are too many variables

49:34.437 --> 49:35.969
to consider right now.

49:35.971 --> 49:37.937
[SCOFFS]
So, what are we gonna do?

49:37.939 --> 49:41.341
Sit here and twiddle our thumbs
while those bastards run riot?

49:41.343 --> 49:42.942
Bergen.

49:42.944 --> 49:46.480
We have never allowed a prisoner
to escape from this jail.

49:46.482 --> 49:48.281
Do you really think
I'm gonna allow

49:48.283 --> 49:50.350
these prisoners
to change that reputation?

49:50.352 --> 49:51.787
No, sir.

49:53.723 --> 49:57.424
So as it says
in Romans 13:4,

49:57.426 --> 50:00.828
"But if you do wrong,
be afraid,

50:00.830 --> 50:02.996
for he does not
bear the sword in vain.

50:02.998 --> 50:05.699
For he is a servant
of the Lord,

50:05.701 --> 50:08.939
an avenger who carries out
God's wrath on the wrongdoer."

50:10.439 --> 50:13.475
So, what's our next move,
sir?

50:14.576 --> 50:16.944
Call General Stillwell.

50:16.946 --> 50:19.746
It's time to bring in
the military.

50:19.748 --> 50:22.650
[♪♪♪]

50:22.652 --> 50:24.717
This is your final chance.

50:24.719 --> 50:26.886
All of you.

50:26.888 --> 50:28.589
Where is the key?

50:28.591 --> 50:31.328
I told you, we didn't have it
in the first place.

50:32.460 --> 50:33.861
Lageson?

50:33.863 --> 50:35.596
God's truth, Joe.

50:35.598 --> 50:37.464
All the keys I had
were on that belt.

50:37.466 --> 50:39.536
[LAUGHING]

50:42.937 --> 50:44.504
Shoot this piece of shit.

50:44.506 --> 50:47.007
Whoa, let's not make
any rash moves here,

50:47.009 --> 50:48.609
he could still
be useful to us.

50:48.611 --> 50:50.911
Shoot him, Clarence.
Shoot him dead.

50:50.913 --> 50:52.712
What?

50:52.714 --> 50:58.384
Put one between his eyes,
right here, now!

50:58.386 --> 51:00.054
Come on, Clarence!

51:00.056 --> 51:01.992
[♪♪♪]

51:05.727 --> 51:07.696
JOE:
Come on, Clarence, huh?

51:09.732 --> 51:12.598
That's it, that's it.

51:12.600 --> 51:14.634
Come on, Clarence.

51:14.636 --> 51:15.772
Do it.

51:17.605 --> 51:19.005
Clarence, don't do it.

51:19.007 --> 51:20.708
What are you,
the fuckin' boss?

51:20.710 --> 51:22.442
This is my fuckin' idea.

51:22.444 --> 51:24.645
Yeah, it was your idea,
this totally...

51:24.647 --> 51:26.283
[MEN GRUNTING]

51:29.085 --> 51:31.417
JOE:
Let the kid fight it out.

51:31.419 --> 51:33.622
Come on!
Come on, Clarence.

51:34.656 --> 51:36.556
Wanna go, kid?

51:36.558 --> 51:38.558
You will not...
Mr. Clarence.

51:38.560 --> 51:40.497
- Yeah!
- [GRUNTING]

51:47.469 --> 51:49.469
[GRUNTING]

51:49.471 --> 51:50.971
JOE:
Oh, that's the kid.

51:50.973 --> 51:53.310
Choke him.
Choke that motherfucker.

51:54.676 --> 51:57.411
- Choke him. Choke him. Choke him.
- [GRUNTING]

51:57.413 --> 51:58.978
Come on, Clarence!

51:58.980 --> 52:02.415
Yeah!
Come on, come on, that's my boy.

52:02.417 --> 52:03.850
Yeah!

52:03.852 --> 52:05.087
[BOTH GRUNTING]

52:06.455 --> 52:07.857
JOE:
Yeah!

52:11.960 --> 52:14.596
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah!

52:17.767 --> 52:19.902
[GASPS]

52:22.772 --> 52:24.974
That's my fucking boy.

52:29.978 --> 52:31.848
That's my fucking boy.

52:35.817 --> 52:37.717
Put him out of his misery.

52:37.719 --> 52:40.087
[♪♪♪]

52:40.089 --> 52:41.024
Yeah.

52:44.893 --> 52:47.694
Put him out of his misery,
or I'll put you out of yours.

52:47.696 --> 52:49.096
- Joe!
- Shut the fuck up, Bern.

52:49.098 --> 52:51.498
This got nothin'
to do with you.

52:51.500 --> 52:53.466
Now do it, kid.

52:53.468 --> 52:55.404
[♪♪♪]

53:06.114 --> 53:08.047
[GUNSHOT]

53:08.049 --> 53:09.685
JOE:
That's my boy.

53:13.756 --> 53:15.221
That's my boy.

53:15.223 --> 53:16.759
Congratulations.

53:18.761 --> 53:20.430
BERNIE:
Well, that's just great.

53:21.629 --> 53:23.999
- Now what?
- "Now what"?

53:26.734 --> 53:27.836
Marv?

53:35.544 --> 53:36.710
OFFICER:
No!

53:36.712 --> 53:38.812
Oh!

53:38.814 --> 53:41.214
Joe! What the fuck?

53:41.216 --> 53:42.618
Sam.

53:45.520 --> 53:47.122
No, no.

53:48.524 --> 53:50.056
- Joe...
- It's all right, Weinhold.

53:50.058 --> 53:51.692
Joe, you don't
have to do this.

53:51.694 --> 53:52.926
It's all right.

53:52.928 --> 53:54.795
I'm gonna let you go.
It's all right.

53:54.797 --> 53:56.196
It's all right. Come on.

53:56.198 --> 53:58.868
Yeah, yeah, come on.

53:59.268 --> 54:00.634
Give me a hug.

54:00.636 --> 54:03.170
I'm sorry, shush.

54:03.172 --> 54:05.272
Shush, shush, that's it.

54:05.274 --> 54:07.207
That's my boy.

54:07.209 --> 54:10.013
That's it, it's okay,
it's okay.

54:11.779 --> 54:14.950
It's all right,
yeah, it's all right.

54:16.085 --> 54:17.250
It's all right.

54:17.252 --> 54:18.520
[GUNSHOT]

54:26.895 --> 54:28.897
[CHUCKLING]

54:31.567 --> 54:33.766
Why the long faces?

54:33.768 --> 54:35.569
Motherfuckers deserved it.

54:35.571 --> 54:37.703
You think they'd a shown us
any mercy

54:37.705 --> 54:39.038
if roles were reversed?

54:39.040 --> 54:40.243
Fuck, no.

54:41.910 --> 54:43.512
Nice one, Joe.

54:47.850 --> 54:51.585
There are five prisoners we know
of involved in the disturbance.

54:51.587 --> 54:53.719
Their leader appears to be
Joseph Christopher.

54:53.721 --> 54:54.922
His background...

54:54.924 --> 54:57.024
Let me stop you
right there, Warden.

54:57.026 --> 55:00.060
I don't need to know
where these men came from,

55:00.062 --> 55:02.062
I only need to know
where they're going.

55:02.064 --> 55:03.696
And that's straight to hell.

55:03.698 --> 55:06.632
The eyes of a nation
are upon us.

55:06.634 --> 55:08.835
The hopes and prayers
of liberty-loving people

55:08.837 --> 55:11.772
everywhere
march with us in this moment.

55:11.774 --> 55:15.174
I haven't come here to issue
an order to hold our position.

55:15.176 --> 55:17.277
I'm not holding
a goddamn thing.

55:17.279 --> 55:19.245
Except the enemy...
by the balls.

55:19.247 --> 55:21.647
Our ultimate goal here
is to regain control

55:21.649 --> 55:25.319
of this institution and send
a big clear message

55:25.321 --> 55:28.589
that you fuck with Alcatraz,

55:28.591 --> 55:30.924
Alcatraz will fuck with you.

55:30.926 --> 55:32.862
[♪♪♪]

55:42.036 --> 55:45.040
JOE: You know, there's something
I can't get out of my head.

55:46.875 --> 55:48.641
Oh, yeah?

55:48.643 --> 55:51.277
What's that?

55:51.279 --> 55:55.852
JOE: I've always been proud
of my ability to spot a liar.

55:56.884 --> 55:59.319
[SCOFFS]

55:59.321 --> 56:03.290
My mother,
may she rest in peace,

56:03.292 --> 56:06.696
would say,
"Takes one to know one."

56:09.297 --> 56:12.701
And I know my instinct
has never betrayed me.

56:18.906 --> 56:23.810
When Weinhold and Miller
said they didn't have the keys,

56:23.812 --> 56:25.714
they were telling the truth.

56:26.948 --> 56:29.017
They never had the keys.

56:39.328 --> 56:43.032
The real kicker is
Lageson.

56:44.866 --> 56:48.870
That motherfucker was convinced
those keys were on his belt.

56:50.406 --> 56:52.976
So what are you sayin', Joe?

57:00.015 --> 57:02.051
We got a traitor in our midst.

57:03.951 --> 57:05.888
[♪♪♪]

57:13.027 --> 57:16.830
Oh, come on,
you're just being paranoid.

57:16.832 --> 57:18.864
Am I, Bern?

57:18.866 --> 57:20.067
BERNIE:
Yeah.

57:20.069 --> 57:22.169
Well,
someone's fucked me over,

57:22.171 --> 57:24.804
and I ain't never
been fucked over.

57:24.806 --> 57:27.643
And I'm gonna figure out
who the fuck it is.

57:47.096 --> 57:48.297
[WHISPERS]
Miller?

57:51.799 --> 57:52.901
Miller?

58:47.089 --> 58:48.123
[GRUNTING QUIETLY]

58:49.892 --> 58:51.223
[SHUSHING]

58:51.225 --> 58:52.993
Be quiet.

58:52.995 --> 58:54.063
Be quiet.

58:55.564 --> 58:59.035
Be quiet.
You have to be quiet.

59:13.381 --> 59:14.580
Can you lift your hands?

59:14.582 --> 59:16.351
[PANTING]

59:18.352 --> 59:21.289
You keep the pressure on that,
you keep it tight.

59:43.212 --> 59:45.014
[PANTING]

59:48.250 --> 59:49.886
Okay, okay, okay.

59:52.486 --> 59:54.587
You two will advance
on the west side

59:54.589 --> 59:58.391
exterior of cell block B,
there's a window position there.

59:58.393 --> 01:00:01.127
I want you to drop
two grenades in.

01:00:01.129 --> 01:00:03.096
You two, same process,
but the west side

01:00:03.098 --> 01:00:05.031
exterior in cell block A.

01:00:05.033 --> 01:00:07.100
Two more grenades
in that section.

01:00:07.102 --> 01:00:08.400
Now, they'll have a choice.

01:00:08.402 --> 01:00:10.237
When they see those
grenades come in,

01:00:10.239 --> 01:00:13.138
they can either remain there
and be blown to kingdom come,

01:00:13.140 --> 01:00:15.040
or they can run back
into the corridor

01:00:15.042 --> 01:00:17.310
that leads to cell block C.

01:00:17.312 --> 01:00:19.578
You two will be positioned
in cell block C.

01:00:19.580 --> 01:00:21.448
Soon as those
sons of bitches enter,

01:00:21.450 --> 01:00:23.315
I want you to fill
them so full of holes,

01:00:23.317 --> 01:00:25.118
they'll whistle as they fall.

01:00:25.120 --> 01:00:27.654
Bergen, I want you
to take up a sniper's position

01:00:27.656 --> 01:00:29.388
here
in the warden's office.

01:00:29.390 --> 01:00:32.091
That window has a commanding
view of the whole yard.

01:00:32.093 --> 01:00:35.228
And if by some miracle
those bastards make it that far,

01:00:35.230 --> 01:00:37.630
shoot. And shoot to kill.

01:00:37.632 --> 01:00:39.098
Got it.

01:00:39.100 --> 01:00:40.902
Okay, let's go!

01:01:00.388 --> 01:01:05.327
You know, they say it's
the quiet ones you gotta watch.

01:01:07.062 --> 01:01:08.464
What do you say, Marv?

01:01:09.497 --> 01:01:11.665
You havin' yourself a little

01:01:11.667 --> 01:01:13.969
silent rebellion over here?

01:01:15.536 --> 01:01:18.270
I don't know nothin'
about that key, Joe.

01:01:18.272 --> 01:01:21.042
I wanna get out of here,
same as you.

01:01:43.531 --> 01:01:46.368
Gonna shine a spotlight
on me now, Joe?

01:01:48.437 --> 01:01:50.737
Just givin' you
a day in court, Sam.

01:01:50.739 --> 01:01:52.642
I think you deserve that.

01:01:54.343 --> 01:01:56.609
So, what do you gotta say
about this here?

01:01:56.611 --> 01:01:58.915
I'm not a fucking traitor.

01:02:00.147 --> 01:02:02.017
JOE:
So we agree there is one?

01:02:03.585 --> 01:02:06.152
Look, I don't know
about that, Joe.

01:02:06.154 --> 01:02:07.219
[SCOFFS]

01:02:07.221 --> 01:02:09.091
You want my two cents?

01:02:10.558 --> 01:02:12.625
I thought we all came along
on this thing

01:02:12.627 --> 01:02:15.728
'cause we wanted
the fuck out of this place.

01:02:15.730 --> 01:02:20.000
Makes no sense to hide a key
and grind this shit to a halt.

01:02:20.002 --> 01:02:21.533
Why would anyone do that?

01:02:21.535 --> 01:02:24.172
Well, hell, Sam,
I don't know.

01:02:27.075 --> 01:02:30.643
Maybe someone's not happy
with the current leadership!

01:02:30.645 --> 01:02:32.681
Someone's disgruntled,
perhaps.

01:02:34.149 --> 01:02:36.281
Somebody wants to stay here

01:02:36.283 --> 01:02:39.685
and make a play
for the leadership!

01:02:39.687 --> 01:02:43.123
Better to reign in hell
than serve in heaven.

01:02:43.125 --> 01:02:45.225
You think I wanna
be the leader, Joe?

01:02:45.227 --> 01:02:48.527
Well, if you do, Sam,
you remember this,

01:02:48.529 --> 01:02:52.332
heavy lies the head
that wears the crown.

01:02:52.334 --> 01:02:56.169
How many people have I clipped
on your say-so, Joe?

01:02:56.171 --> 01:02:59.772
Shit, I'd take my own mother out
if you gave me the nod.

01:02:59.774 --> 01:03:02.775
And you're gonna stand there
and question my loyalty?

01:03:02.777 --> 01:03:04.743
I wasn't disgruntled before,

01:03:04.745 --> 01:03:08.183
but I fucking am now,
you crazy fuck!

01:03:14.189 --> 01:03:15.623
All right, Sam.

01:03:18.160 --> 01:03:20.393
[PATTING]

01:03:20.395 --> 01:03:21.530
All right, Sam.

01:03:23.297 --> 01:03:24.566
Take it easy.

01:03:28.536 --> 01:03:30.473
[♪♪♪]

01:03:40.515 --> 01:03:43.551
[GRUNTING, PANTING]

01:03:50.658 --> 01:03:52.427
[DOOR KNOB RATTLING]

01:04:32.366 --> 01:04:36.870
So, what do you gotta
say about this, Bern?

01:04:36.872 --> 01:04:38.774
Not a lot, Joe.

01:04:42.777 --> 01:04:46.245
We haven't been seeing
eye to eye recently, have we?

01:04:46.247 --> 01:04:48.348
Planning this shit
ain't been easy,

01:04:48.350 --> 01:04:51.120
it's a lot of tension
flying around.

01:04:53.587 --> 01:04:56.589
You wanna get
out of here, Bern?

01:04:56.591 --> 01:04:59.527
Of course I fucking do,
this whole thing's my idea.

01:05:01.163 --> 01:05:02.231
True.

01:05:03.598 --> 01:05:05.500
But maybe you got cold feet.

01:05:07.636 --> 01:05:11.237
Maybe your eyes are bigger
than your balls.

01:05:11.239 --> 01:05:14.274
Maybe an institutionalized
old fuck like you

01:05:14.276 --> 01:05:18.478
realized life on the outside
was pretty fucking daunting.

01:05:18.480 --> 01:05:21.915
You know, Joe,
if you're on a mission

01:05:21.917 --> 01:05:24.616
to piss off every member
of your crew,

01:05:24.618 --> 01:05:27.722
well, you fuckin' succeeded.

01:05:30.625 --> 01:05:33.393
You're a clever man, Bern.

01:05:33.395 --> 01:05:35.495
You've given me
a lot of words,

01:05:35.497 --> 01:05:37.799
but you haven't given me
the right answer.

01:05:39.533 --> 01:05:43.835
No, Joe, I didn't take
the fucking key.

01:05:43.837 --> 01:05:45.471
Happy now?

01:05:45.473 --> 01:05:46.542
Jesus.

01:06:00.821 --> 01:06:02.323
[CLICKS TONGUE]

01:06:07.328 --> 01:06:10.362
What do you gotta say,
kid?

01:06:10.364 --> 01:06:12.899
You've been the source
of some of the shit

01:06:12.901 --> 01:06:14.803
between me and Bern recently.

01:06:16.671 --> 01:06:18.873
Look, Joe,
that was never my intention.

01:06:19.741 --> 01:06:21.373
[SCOFFS]

01:06:21.375 --> 01:06:24.509
It ain't your fault.

01:06:24.511 --> 01:06:27.480
Old Bern here
has a good heart.

01:06:27.482 --> 01:06:32.585
Took you under his wing,
took care of you.

01:06:32.587 --> 01:06:34.890
Real nice of him,
don't you think?

01:06:36.558 --> 01:06:38.826
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

01:06:40.495 --> 01:06:42.765
He's a real stand-up guy.

01:06:44.866 --> 01:06:50.569
But here's the thing. He's been
in a criminal life for decades,

01:06:50.571 --> 01:06:54.910
and he's never risen above
your standard foot soldier.

01:06:58.546 --> 01:07:00.315
Why do you think that is?

01:07:01.850 --> 01:07:04.449
I don't know, Joe,
maybe he didn't want it.

01:07:04.451 --> 01:07:06.786
Oh, I think he did.

01:07:06.788 --> 01:07:09.989
The reason why he'd never been

01:07:09.991 --> 01:07:11.994
a contender
for the top seat is...

01:07:13.694 --> 01:07:16.562
his judgment
is fuckin' suspect.

01:07:16.564 --> 01:07:18.797
[SCREAMS]
What am I supposed to do?

01:07:18.799 --> 01:07:20.900
Just stand there
while you talk about me

01:07:20.902 --> 01:07:22.402
like I'm not even here?

01:07:22.404 --> 01:07:23.906
Back against the wall,
Bern.

01:07:24.906 --> 01:07:26.275
Get back!

01:07:31.779 --> 01:07:33.448
[♪♪♪]

01:07:41.955 --> 01:07:44.759
- [RADIO STATIC CRACKLES]
- GENERAL: Received, over.

01:07:48.096 --> 01:07:49.398
Await my command.

01:07:51.366 --> 01:07:54.033
[♪♪♪]

01:07:54.035 --> 01:07:56.437
Let's get down
to brass tacks, kid.

01:07:57.806 --> 01:07:59.708
I've known these guys
for years.

01:08:01.343 --> 01:08:03.009
When you do real time
with someone,

01:08:03.011 --> 01:08:04.944
you really get to know them.

01:08:04.946 --> 01:08:07.950
You've only been here
a month or two.

01:08:09.750 --> 01:08:13.786
And I'm just wondering
if you can let a broken down

01:08:13.788 --> 01:08:16.388
old fuck like that
get in your ear,

01:08:16.390 --> 01:08:18.658
who else could get in there?

01:08:18.660 --> 01:08:22.361
I don't know
what you're talking about, Joe.

01:08:22.363 --> 01:08:24.629
Your meetin' you had
with the warden.

01:08:24.631 --> 01:08:28.633
First thing I fucking did was
come and tell you guys about it.

01:08:28.635 --> 01:08:30.435
That don't mean nothin'!

01:08:30.438 --> 01:08:32.537
Could be just
covering your tracks.

01:08:32.540 --> 01:08:34.310
Covering my tracks on what?

01:08:35.443 --> 01:08:36.875
Being the warden's snitch.

01:08:36.877 --> 01:08:38.444
What the fuck?

01:08:38.446 --> 01:08:41.513
Well, somethin'
don't smell right!

01:08:41.515 --> 01:08:43.816
Somethin' don't
fuckin' smell right!

01:08:43.818 --> 01:08:46.417
The way we fuckin'
planned this

01:08:46.420 --> 01:08:50.087
we had a 10-minute gap
before that siren went off!

01:08:50.090 --> 01:08:51.624
When we grabbed those guns,

01:08:51.626 --> 01:08:53.526
that armed response
was right there!

01:08:53.528 --> 01:08:55.560
What you think
I'm the fuckin' rat, Joe?

01:08:55.563 --> 01:08:58.462
Well, it makes fuckin' sense,
don't it?

01:08:58.465 --> 01:09:00.533
What'd the warden tell ya,
huh?

01:09:00.535 --> 01:09:03.136
Put skids on the operation,
you get a reduced sentence?

01:09:03.138 --> 01:09:05.837
- You lost your goddamn mind.
- Yeah!

01:09:05.840 --> 01:09:07.640
That's the old way
down for you.

01:09:07.642 --> 01:09:10.709
You know what, I shoulda smashed
your fucking ears

01:09:10.711 --> 01:09:12.645
the moment
this shit started.

01:09:12.647 --> 01:09:13.814
You fucking rat!

01:09:18.519 --> 01:09:20.484
What the fuck?

01:09:20.487 --> 01:09:23.423
You're making
a big fucking mistake, Joe.

01:09:23.425 --> 01:09:24.990
Whoa, come on, guys.

01:09:24.992 --> 01:09:28.194
Bern, how many fucking years
have we known each other?

01:09:28.196 --> 01:09:30.729
It doesn't have to be
this way, man.

01:09:30.732 --> 01:09:32.596
Well, you shoulda
thought of that

01:09:32.599 --> 01:09:34.167
before you pulled
a gun on the kid.

01:09:34.169 --> 01:09:37.035
JOE [BREATHING HEAVILY]:
Fuck.

01:09:37.037 --> 01:09:40.106
Come on, Bern,
the kid's a fuckin' rat.

01:09:40.108 --> 01:09:41.740
He's a fuckin' rat, Bern!

01:09:41.742 --> 01:09:43.776
You're wrong, Joe.

01:09:43.778 --> 01:09:46.111
The kid may be many things,
but he ain't no rat.

01:09:46.113 --> 01:09:48.113
JOE: Kid's a fuckin'
rat, he's 'bout to go

01:09:48.116 --> 01:09:49.548
down with the dirt now.

01:09:49.550 --> 01:09:51.517
Shoot him, I'll put a bullet

01:09:51.519 --> 01:09:52.917
in the back of your skull.

01:09:52.920 --> 01:09:55.588
And I'll put a bullet
in the back of yours.

01:09:55.590 --> 01:09:58.894
Put the gun down, Bernie,
and back the fuck off.

01:10:00.461 --> 01:10:01.793
BERNIE:
Fuck you.

